               <msContents>
                  <summary source="#allegro"> Part of the Book of the Dead showing the right-hand part of the
                     vignette of Spell 125 "The Weighing of the Heart in the Hall of the Double Truth"
                     before Osiris, the King of the Dead. The text is missing only the illustration is included.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="egy-Egyh">Egyptian in Hieratic script</textLang>

               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="sheet">
                     <supportDesc material="papyrus">
                        <support>Papyrus</support>
                        <extent>1 fragment of papyrus. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>188</height>
                              <width>510</width>
                           </dimensions></extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote>Likely written by one scribe, all in black ink.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>From left to right: Ammut sat on a pedestal, Horus and Anubis tending
                        to the scales, which weigh a Maat feather against a heart. Above the scales
                        are a monkey and two forms of the goddess Meskhenet, depicted as birthing
                        bricks with heads. A woman (Isis-Weret, the owner of this copy of the Book
                        of the Dead), holds a Maat feather, while the goddess Maat stands behind
                        her. Outside the shrine are 24 seated deities, all wearing Maat-feather
                        headdresses and holding was-sceptres. Illustrated in black ink
                        only.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>

               </physDesc>
